metadata.description:
issued a tearing cry.



Fortunately, the fire lasted only a few minutes before it began to spread deeper into the field, but those few minutes were the worst of their lives for many soldiers.



"Chi Guo, are you all right?"



Zhao Zhiguo was picking at his ear, which was almost blocked by mud, and his memory was in chaos. The scene in front of him was both familiar and strange to him. He was quite sure that this was the bloody battlefield he had experienced countless times, but it was too different from what he had experienced.
